I. FREDERICK BADENHOP, Plaintiff and Appellant, v. THOMAS J. CAHILL et al., Defendants and Respondents. Appeal, from a judgment in favor of the defendants entered by the court.

*571Before Barbour, Ch. J., Curtis and Sedgwick, JJ,

Decided April 5, 1873. C. C. Egan, for appellant. B. F. M. Cahill, for respondents. Judgment reversed, and new trial ordered.

Opinion by Curtis, J. Barbour, Ch. J., and Sedgwick, J., concurred.
